67template <typename T>
68std::string ToStringAsDouble(const T value) {
69 // JSON represents numbers as floating point numbers with about 15 decimal
70 // digits of precision.
71 char buf[32];
72 const int len = std::snprintf(&buf[0], arraysize(buf), "%.16g",
73 static_cast<double>(value));
74 RTC_DCHECK_LE(len, arraysize(buf));
75 return std::string(&buf[0], len);
76}

93bool RTCStats::operator==(const RTCStats& other) const {
94 if (type() != other.type() || id() != other.id())
95 return false;
96 std::vector<const RTCStatsMemberInterface*> members = Members();
97 std::vector<const RTCStatsMemberInterface*> other_members = other.Members();
98 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(members.size(), other_members.size());
99 for (size_t i = 0; i < members.size(); ++i) {
100 const RTCStatsMemberInterface* member = members[i];
101 const RTCStatsMemberInterface* other_member = other_members[i];
102 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(member->type(), other_member->type());
103 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(member->name(), other_member->name());
104 if (*member != *other_member)
105 return false;
106 }
107 return true;
108}

114std::string RTCStats::ToJson() const {
115 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
116 sb << "{\"type\":\"" << type()
117 << "\","
118 "\"id\":\""
119 << id_
120 << "\","
121 "\"timestamp\":"
122 << timestamp_us_;
123 for (const RTCStatsMemberInterface* member : Members()) {
124 if (member->is_defined()) {
125 sb << ",\"" << member->name() << "\":";
126 if (member->is_string())
127 sb << "\"" << member->ValueToJson() << "\"";
128 else
129 sb << member->ValueToJson();
130 }
131 }
132 sb << "}";
133 return sb.Release();
